Rectangle inlet (compressible, mass-flow driven)
================================================

Same geometry as rectangle_incompress_U/, but run with the
compressible foamRun "fluid" solver and driven by a target mass flow
rate instead of a target mean velocity. Exercises every code path in
the syntheticTurbulenceInlet that depends on the looked-up rho patch
field (phi has units of kg/s here, so rhoOnPatch returns the rho
volScalarField rather than the constant rhoInf).

Geometry            Rectangle (single block, area = 4.2e-4 m^2).
Inlet target        massFlow = 5e-3 kg/s
                    (equivalent to Umean ~ 10 m/s for air at 1 atm,
                    300 K).
Friction velocity   Auto-computed from the bulk Reynolds number.
Solver              foamRun, fluid (compressible LES, WALE).
Working fluid       Air at 300 K, 1 atm (perfect gas, mu = 1.8e-5,
                    Pr = 0.7, Cv = 712, molWeight = 28.9).

Run with:           ./Allrun
Clean with:         ./Allclean

Notes
-----
For the incompressible / Umean-driven version of the same geometry
see rectangle_incompress_U/. The boundary condition itself is the
same in both tutorials; the differences are (a) which density it
picks up internally (rhoInf vs the rho patch field) and (b) whether
"Umean" or "massFlow" is the driving input.
